.TH LIGHTS2SHAPE 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
lights2shape \- build city\(hylights polygons from a nighttime lights raster
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lights2shape
.RI [ options ]
.I shapename
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lights2shape
reads the nighttime city\(hylights raster (30\(hysecond resolution,
covering latitudes \(+-75), contours intensities at the requested levels
and writes the resulting polygons as an ESRI shapefile. The path to
the lights binary is read from the
.B rasters::lights
setting in the SmartMet configuration. Compressed
.RB ( .gz ", " .bz2 )
inputs are decompressed transparently.
.PP
Each output polygon carries an integer
.B INTENSITY
attribute equal to the level it was generated from. The default
bounding box is suitable for Scandinavia and is automatically clamped
to \(+-75\(de of latitude.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print help.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode.
.TP
.BI \-b " x1,y1,x2,y2"
Bounding box (longitude/latitude) to extract. Default is roughly
Scandinavia
.RI ( 6,51,49,71 ).
.TP
.BI \-l " l1,l2,..."
Comma\(hyseparated list of intensity levels at which to contour.
Default is
.IR 32 .
.SH EXAMPLES
Default Scandinavian lights at intensity 32:
.PP
.RS 4
lights2shape lights
.RE
.PP
European area at multiple intensities:
.PP
.RS 4
lights2shape \-b \-25,35,45,72 \-l 16,32,64 europe_lights
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR etopo2shape (1),
.BR shape2ps (1),
.BR shapefilter (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-shapetools/issues>.
